{
  "texts": [
    "In practice, this analysis process often requires a significant investment of time and computational resources, especially when dealing with large-scale graph data.",
    "Therefore, the development of efficient and intelligent hyperparameter optimization strategies to reduce the computational effort of sensitivity analysis is an important direction in the field of graph pooling research.",
    "With these strategies, near-optimal combinations of hyperparameters can be found in a shorter time, which improves the performance of graph pooling models and accelerates their deployment in real applications.",
    "In the section on the frontier, we provide a detailed description of the taxonomy of graph pooling methods as well as previous research works.",
    "To allow researchers to better select and apply graph pooling methods, Table 9 summarizes the key characteristics of representative graph pooling techniques, including year, reasons for selection, computational efficiency, scalability, popularity, plus aspects, and minus aspects."
  ]
}